 176:../../Middlewares/LVGL/GUI/lvgl/src/draw/sw/lv_draw_sw_transform.c ****     /*If scaled only make some simplification to avoid rounding errors.
 177:../../Middlewares/LVGL/GUI/lvgl/src/draw/sw/lv_draw_sw_transform.c ****      *For example if there is a 100x100 image zoomed to 300%
 178:../../Middlewares/LVGL/GUI/lvgl/src/draw/sw/lv_draw_sw_transform.c ****      *The destination area in X will be x1=0; x2=299
 179:../../Middlewares/LVGL/GUI/lvgl/src/draw/sw/lv_draw_sw_transform.c ****      *When the step is calculated below it will think that stepping
 180:../../Middlewares/LVGL/GUI/lvgl/src/draw/sw/lv_draw_sw_transform.c ****      *1/3 pixels on the original image will result in 300% zoom.
 181:../../Middlewares/LVGL/GUI/lvgl/src/draw/sw/lv_draw_sw_transform.c ****      *However this way the last pixel will be on the 99.67 coordinate.
 182:../../Middlewares/LVGL/GUI/lvgl/src/draw/sw/lv_draw_sw_transform.c ****      *As it's larger than 99.5 LVGL will start to mix the next coordinate
 183:../../Middlewares/LVGL/GUI/lvgl/src/draw/sw/lv_draw_sw_transform.c ****      *which is out of the image, so will make the pixel more transparent.
